    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You conjure weaving rough winds to throw an enemy off balance or even throw them into the air.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">  </span>The range for this spell varies depending on the number of actions used to cast this spell:</p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">         </span></span></span>1 action: You target a creature within 100 feet.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">         </span></span></span>2 actions: You affect creatures in a 20-foot burst within 100 feet of you.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">·<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">         </span></span></span>3 actions: You shape the wind and target up to 6 creatures within a 20-foot radius around you.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Creatures who are targeted must make a basic Reflex saving throw. Airborne creatures who rely on wind to stay aloft treat their outcome as one degree worse.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Success</strong> The creature suffers a -10 circumstance penalty to its speed until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Failure</strong> As success, but the creature is also knocked prone.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As success, but the creature is also thrown 10 feet into the air and falls, taking 5 bludgeoning damage and being knocked prone.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u>Special: </u>While you are in Earthen Rage, the wind cuts your enemies, dealing 2d8 slashing damage as part of a basic Reflex save.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong> </strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The Earthen Rage damage increases by an additional 1d8. Creatures who critically fail are thrown an additional 10 feet up, suffering an additional 5 bludgeoning damage when they fall.</p>"
    },
